===Noun===
'''salt''' (''[[uncountable]] and [[countable]]; plural:'' '''[[salts]]''')

# A [[compound]] formed from the [[reaction]] of an [[acid]] with a [[base]], where a positive [[ion]] replaces a [[hydrogen]] of the acid.
# General term for [[sodium chloride]] ([[NaCl]]) (also ''common salt'').
# A [[marsh]] (also [[salt-marsh]])
# ''(slang):'' A [[sailor]] (also ''old salt'').
# ''([[cryptography]]):'' additional [[bytes]] inserted into a term to increase [[randomness]] and obscure [[algorithm]] either before or after a step of [[encryption]].

